name: Matcha Green Tea Cake
author: Lumineer Academy
summary: This is how to make a soft, moist, and delicious green tea cake that can be warmed up again and again.
ingredients: 1 ½ tablespoons matcha green tea powder
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Combine eggs, 2 egg whites, and 3/4 cup egg whites in a large bowl; beat with an electric mixer until thick and doubled in volume
Add ingredients one at a time, beating 15 to 30 seconds after each addition, in the following order: sugar, honey, flour, baking powder, matcha, vanilla extract, butter, and buttermilk
Pour batter into the prepared baking dish
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes
